<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17640728-30">
               <interp inst="t17640728-30" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640728-30" type="year" value="1764"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640728-30" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17640728"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640728-30" type="date" value="17640728"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17640728-30-off153-c187" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640728-30-defend255 t17640728-30-off153 t17640728-30-verdict156"></join>
         
               <p>426. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17640728-30-defend255" type="defendantName">
                     Martha 
                     Pitney 
                  <interp inst="t17640728-30-defend255" type="surname" value="Pitney"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-30-defend255" type="given" value="Martha"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-30-defend255" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , <rs id="t17640728-30-deflabel152" type="occupation">spinster</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640728-30-defend255 t17640728-30-deflabel152"></join>, was indicted for <rs id="t17640728-30-off153" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640728-30-off153" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-30-off153" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing a silver pint mug, value 36 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17640728-30-victim257" type="victimName">
                     Christopher 
                     Shambrooke 
                  <interp inst="t17640728-30-victim257" type="surname" value="Shambrooke"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-30-victim257" type="given" value="Christopher"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-30-victim257" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640728-30-off153 t17640728-30-victim257"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17640728-30-cd154" type="crimeDate">July 4</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640728-30-off153 t17640728-30-cd154"></join>. *</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17640728-30-person258">
                  Eleanor 
                  Shambrooke 
               <interp inst="t17640728-30-person258" type="surname" value="Shambrooke"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-30-person258" type="given" value="Eleanor"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-30-person258" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am wife to the prosecutor; I keep the <placeName id="t17640728-30-crimeloc155">Windmill public house, in Rosemary-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17640728-30-crimeloc155" type="placeName" value="Windmill public house, in Rosemary-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17640728-30-crimeloc155" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640728-30-off153 t17640728-30-crimeloc155"></join>: the prisoner and another woman came in for a penny worth of beer, on the 4th of June, about four in the afternoon; I went down to draw her beer; then the mug stood upon the dresser; and when I came up again, the mug and prisoner were gone; the other woman was there: I asked<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="176407280013"></xptr> my servants if they had moved the mug; they said no: then I enquired of her friend where she was; she said, she was gone to a friend, and would be back presently: I bid her not trifle with me, for she had got my mug. Then Alice Gaul told me a woman was coming up the passage; I went to the passage; the prisoner was there; I went out and took hold of her, and brought her into the house; I charged her with taking it; she denied it to me, and said, she was coming back with it. (Produced and deposed to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17640728-30-person259">
                  Alice 
                  Gaul 
               <interp inst="t17640728-30-person259" type="surname" value="Gaul"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-30-person259" type="given" value="Alice"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-30-person259" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner coming back; I told the prosecutrix where she was; she came and took her into the house, and I saw her deliver back the mug.</p>
               <p>Q. to Prosecutrix. Was the prisoner a customer before?</p>
               <p>Prosecutrix. I never saw her before to my knowledge.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I met a woman in Rosemary-lane, which I had a very slight acquaintance with; she asked me to go and drink; we went into this house; then she wanted me to go of an errand for her, to a man in the lane: she came after me, and put this mug into my apron. When I saw what it was, I was going to carry it back, and the woman met me; I delivered it to her.</p>
               <p>She called 
               <persName id="t17640728-30-person260">
                  Solomon 
                  Cole 
               <interp inst="t17640728-30-person260" type="surname" value="Cole"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-30-person260" type="given" value="Solomon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-30-person260" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , who had known her fourteen years, and 
               <persName id="t17640728-30-person261">
                  Joseph 
                  Philipson 
               <interp inst="t17640728-30-person261" type="surname" value="Philipson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-30-person261" type="given" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-30-person261" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , who gave her a good character. The latter said he had known her from her infancy; and would take her into his service was she cleared.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17640728-30-verdict156" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640728-30-verdict156" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               Acquitted
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
